C.        Economics Editor (international, 2 person-months, intermittent)  
5.   The economics editor will be responsible for the manuscript editing of the Key Indicators 
special chapter; and assist in preparing the highlights, including the tables and charts included 
in the publication. He or she should have at least a master’s degree in the related field and have 
more than 10 years of experience in writing and editing. He or she will assist in the preparation 
of the highlights and presentation materials for the launch of Key Indicators. 

6.   The work is to review and edit the special theme chapter, statistical commentaries, and 
sources for the graphs and tables of Key Indicators for Asia and the Pacific 2016 in compliance 
with acceptable ADB and international forms of editing and ADB’s Handbook of Style and 
Usage.1 The work includes a number of editing rounds of the typeset version until a desired 
quality is achieved. The editor will also make suggestions regarding the layout of the publication. 
In particular, the manuscript or economics editor will carry out the following for the special chapter 
and highlights: 
(i)  reorganize  the text  so that the  subject matter  is  easy to  understand  and  is 
logically presented; 
(ii)  eliminate wordiness and repetition, and reduce ambiguity;  
(iii)  query substantive discrepancies, possible typographical errors, and non-English 
terms; 
(iv)  edit tables and figures, and recast if required; 
(v)  ensure that subheadings are consistent and logical; 
(vi)  check references to tables, figures, appendixes, and parts of the text; 
(vii)  edit notes to ensure that the text references are correct; 
(viii)  edit reference lists; 
(ix)  edit the foreword and acknowledgment; 
(x)  edit highlights; 
(xi)  check final changes; 
(xii)  work closely with the Key Indicators overall coordinator; 
(xiii)  check and sign off on the layout; and 
(xiv)  perform other relevant tasks as assigned by ERDI. 

7.  The outputs are edited manuscripts of the special chapter, highlights, and presentation 
materials. 


